### [Isaiah Chapter 12](../../../bib/kjv/isa012.htm#001.md)

[Isaiah 12:1](../../../bib/kjv/isa012.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">isa 12:1</span></span>

In that day - When this great work of the reduction of Israel, and
conversion of the Gentiles is fulfilled.

[Isaiah 12:2](../../../bib/kjv/isa012.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">isa 12:2</span></span>

God - My salvation hath not been brought to pass by man, but by the
almighty power of God.

[Isaiah 12:3](../../../bib/kjv/isa012.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">isa 12:3</span></span>

With joy - Your thirsty souls shall be filled with Divine graces and
comforts, which you may draw from God, in the use of gospel -
ordinances.

